declarations.comments:
The SoundFont API which we will expose
the Audio Buffer for a single note
declarations.title: AudioBuffer

declarations.comments: an instrument name attached to its SoundFont
declarations.title: Instrument

declarations.comments: the mapping of instrument names to MIDI channels
declarations.title: InstrumentChannels

declarations.comments: A Midi Note
declarations.title: MidiNote

declarations.comments:
the instrument soundfont
a mapping between MIDI pitch and the note's AudioBuffer
declarations.title: SoundFont

declarations.comments: can the browser play ogg format ?
declarations.title: canPlayOgg

declarations.comments: is the browser web-audio enabled ?
declarations.title: isWebAudioEnabled

declarations.comments:
setting for how long the note 'rings' after it's alloted time
in order to support features such as a more legato feel
This should be a number between 0 (no ring) and 1 (double the original
note duration)
declarations.title: setNoteRing

declarations.comments: just for debug
declarations.title: logLoadResource

declarations.comments:
load a single instrument SoundFont
The options are to load the soundfont from:
  Benjamin Gleitzman's server (default)
  A directory from the local server if this is supplied
declarations.title: loadInstrument

declarations.comments:
load a bunch of instrument SoundFonts (in parallel)
again with options to load either locally or remotely
from Benjamin Gleitzman's server
declarations.title: loadInstruments

declarations.comments: load a bunch of soundfonts from the Gleitzmann server
declarations.title: loadRemoteSoundFonts

declarations.comments: load the piano soundfont from a relative directory on the local server
declarations.title: loadPianoSoundFont

declarations.comments:
play a single note through its soundfont buffer.
if the note cannot be played because it:
   uses an invalid instrument
   has a note index that can't be resolved
then treat the note as a Rest, with its stated duration
declarations.title: playNote

declarations.comments:
play a bunch of notes asynchronously
return the duration of the phrase
(i.e. the time offset plus duration of the last note in the phrase)
declarations.title: playNotes

declarations.comments: create a map of instrument name to channel from an Instrument Array
declarations.title: instrumentChannels

declarations.comments: the final note map indexed by the MIDI pitch number
declarations.title: NoteMap

declarations.comments:
Parse the downloaded MIDI.js and process the JSON if we can.
This MIDI.js format starts with some javascript which we need to ditch
and then the almost-Json for the requested instrument -
unfortunately it leaves a trailing comma before the final brace.
declarations.title: midiJsToNoteMap

declarations.comments:
Provide descriptions of MIDI.js from https://github.com/gleitz/midi-js-soundfonts
which describes each note in terms of its pitch class.
Provide a translation of note names to MIDI note ids.
declarations.title: RecordingFormat

declarations.comments:
this should parse Bb0 into
Just [(Just "Bb0"),(Just "B"),(Just "b"),(Just "0")]
and C8 into
Just [(Just "C8"),(Just "C"),(Just ""),(Just "8")]
declarations.title: gleitzNoteName

declarations.comments: debug
declarations.title: debugNoteName

declarations.comments:
we split up a melody into phrases to allow the player to be
re-rendered after each phrase is played
declarations.title: MidiPhrase

declarations.comments: a Melody is the entity that is played by a MIDI player
declarations.title: Melody

declarations.comments:
transform a Midi.Recording to a MIDI melody using the default
phrase size of 0.6 seconds
declarations.title: toMelody

declarations.comments: transform a Midi.Recording to a MIDI melody with a user-defined phrase size
declarations.title: toMelody_
